content:
How to find and fix bad particle data in a FLIP simulation:

1. Add a Geometry Spreadsheet after the DOP extract:
   - Sort by 'v' (velocity magnitude) to find extreme values
   - Add a column for vector magnitude: vexpressionattrib: length(v@v)

2. Find NaN particles with an Attribute Wrangle:
   if (isnan(v@v.x) || isnan(v@v.y) || isnan(v@v.z)) {
       i@bad = 1;
   }
   Then Blast SOP with 'bad' group to remove them.

3. Clamp particle velocities as a bandaid:
   float spd = length(v@v);
   if (spd > 50.0) v@v *= 50.0/spd;
   (This limits top speed to 50 units without killing particles)

4. Trace the bad particles to their source:
   - Add a Trail SOP to track the trajectory of the bad particle
   - Check if bad particles come from a specific emitter region or time window
